Uncertainty still reigned as South Africa prepares to enter the next phase of a phased reopening strategy although some Covid-19 hot-spots might be required to maintain more stringent restrictions on movement. 

At the close of local trade, the rand quoted 1.07% weaker at R17.62/$, after trading in the range of R17.42/$ - R17.66/$. 

The rand traded firmer early this morning as emerging market sentiment benefited from an improvement in China’s May factory activity. The expected range of the rand against the dollar today is R17.25/$ - R17.60/$. --Iol--